In a 2 quart saucepan, bring pineapple juice to a boil. Stir in curry powder and celery salt, and then add rice and butter. Stir until butter melts and rice does not stick together. Reduce heat to low, cover, and simmer for 10 minutes. Stir rice with a fork to loosen from bottom of pot. Simmer another 3 to 5 minutes, or until done.